org.docheinstein.mp3doctor.commons.adt

Interface ObservableFileWrapper<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the wrapped object
    All Superinterfaces:
    FileWrapper, javafx.beans.Observable, ObservableWrapper<E>, Wrapper<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MusicArtistObservableFileWrapper

    public interface ObservableFileWrapper<E>
extends ObservableWrapper<E>, FileWrapper
    Represents an ObservableWrapper of a an object whose changes can be listened via the Observable interface, which this interface extends.

    Furthermore, this interface represents a wrapper of a file and thus is able to retrieve the wrapped file via FileWrapper.getWrappedFile().

    This interface is handy when there is an object in memory which should remain consistent with its representation on the disk.
